{"compliance_id": "383987da-e72c-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a", "document_type": "Incident", "document_url": "https://data.epa.ie/leap/api/v1/Incident/byid?incident_id=383987da-e72c-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a", "title": "", "description": "On the 6th of May 2025 total suspended solids emission limit exceedances at W1 were reported to the site by our offsite contract laboratory.  The incinerator effluent (W1) composite samples collected on 02/05/25 to 07/05/25 showed TSS results of 50mg/l, 154mg/l, 160mg/l, 76mg/l, 114mg/l and 132mg/l respectively which are above the emission limit value of 30mg/l.  

Once the analysis results were reviewed by site on the 07th of May, pump outs via SW01 were suspended and investigation commenced.  A faulty non-return valve located between the wastewater treatment plant and the W1 sampler was identified.  The faulty non-return valve allowed effluent from the waste water treatment plant to flow into the W1 sampler.  The valve was repaired by engineering operations on the 08th of May.
", "submission_date": "", "status": "Open", "metadata": "{"incidentid": "383987da-e72c-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a", "type": "Incident", "reference": "INCI030289", "subject": "Breach of ELV", "status": "Open", "licenceid": "77036c17-572a-4b35-a68c-7e8d9d2bfc03", "licenceprofileid": "1a507022-d459-4a98-afb9-cc0587998ac1", "complianceinvestigationid": null, "incidentcategory": "1. Minor", "nature": "Breach of ELV", "vulnerablereceptors": "Cork Harbour special area of protection (SPA code:004030)", "receptors": "Water", "likelihoodofreoccurence": "Low", "likelycause": "Faulty non-return valve", "newrecurring": "New", "datenotified": "2025-05-09T00:00:00", "closeddate": null, "approximatestart": "2025-05-02T00:00:00", "firstnoticed": "2025-05-07T00:00:00", "finishtime": "2025-05-07T00:00:00", "notifiedparties": "", "dischargepoint": "Yes", "emissionpointname": "P0004-W1", "uncontrolledrelease": "n/a", "description": "On the 6th of May 2025 total suspended solids emission limit exceedances at W1 were reported to the site by our offsite contract laboratory.  The incinerator effluent (W1) composite samples collected on 02/05/25 to 07/05/25 showed TSS results of 50mg/l, 154mg/l, 160mg/l, 76mg/l, 114mg/l and 132mg/l respectively which are above the emission limit value of 30mg/l.  \r\n\r\nOnce the analysis results were reviewed by site on the 07th of May, pump outs via SW01 were suspended and investigation commenced.  A faulty non-return valve located between the wastewater treatment plant and the W1 sampler was identified.  The faulty non-return valve allowed effluent from the waste water treatment plant to flow into the W1 sampler.  The valve was repaired by engineering operations on the 08th of May.\r\n", "otherrelevantinformation": null, "impactonenvironment": "The impact on the environment is expected to be minimal.  W1 is the site incinerator effluent which is then mixed with final effluent prior to discharge via SW01.     \r\nFinal effluent (SW01) results are displayed below:\r\nOn the 2nd of May 44.5kg/day of TSS discharged.\r\nOn the 3rd of May 38.8kg/day of TSS and 379.4kg/day of COD discharged.\r\nOn the 4th of May 45.2kg/day of TSS and 343.7kg/day of COD discharged.\r\nOn the 5th of May 25.3kg/day of TSS and 168kg/day of COD discharged\r\nOn the 6th of May 65.7kg/day of TSS discharged.\r\nOn the 07th of May 86.73kg/day of TSS discharged.\r\nOn the 08th of May 50kg/day of TSS discharged.\r\nThe concentration limit for TSS on SW01 is 35mg/l.  The mass emission limit for TSS at SW01 is 45.5kg/day.  During the incident, this limit was exceeded on 3 days (6th/7th/8th May) and therefore the impact on the environment is expected to be limited.\r\nThe concentration limit for COD on SW01 is 500mg/l.  The mass emission limit for COD at SW01 is 650kg/day.  During this incident, the mass emission limit was not exceeded and therefore no adverse environmental impact is expected.\r\n\r\n", "activityinprogress": "Normal operations", "dischargedetails": null}"}

